title: United Arab Emirates Three Month Interbank Rate
description: United Arab Emirates Three Month Interbank Rate was at 4.08 percent on Tuesday November 8. Interbank Rate in the United Arab Emirates averaged 2.30 percent from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 6.96 percent in June of 2000 and a record low of 0.25 percent in August of 2021. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - United Arab Emirates Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of the UAE
